<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13702] Connect RestClient overrides response status code on request failure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13702</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In case the submitted request status is &amp;gt;=400, the connect RestClient &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/8047ba3800436d6162d0f8eb707e28857ab9eb68/connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/RestClient.java#L133&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/a&gt; a ConnectRestException with the proper response code, but it gets intercepted and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/8047ba3800436d6162d0f8eb707e28857ab9eb68/connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/RestClient.java#L147&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;rethrown with 500 status code&lt;/a&gt;, effectively overriding the actual failure status.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
